1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:12,788
When we practice vipassana, we put ourselves into this very objective place, the objective observer, feeler, and so on.

2
00:00:13,169 --> 00:00:20,335
And to get there, we have to develop that equanimity, sort of non-involvement.

3
00:00:20,435 --> 00:00:25,381
Just as, say, a bird watcher might watch birds, they don't mess around with the bird, they just watch.

4
00:00:26,240 --> 00:00:30,324
And in watching, they begin to understand and see and write a bestseller.

5
00:00:34,152 --> 00:00:36,353
This is how you can start writing your biography.

6
00:00:36,655 --> 00:00:37,536
Your autobiography.

7
00:00:38,377 --> 00:00:39,258
And it was a bestseller.

8
00:00:42,320 --> 00:00:45,804
However, the danger is that this equanimity corrupts into indifference.

9
00:00:47,447 --> 00:00:49,009
And to stop that, we do metta.

10
00:00:49,448 --> 00:00:55,274
Metta re-engages with the psychophysical organism and from there into daily life.

11
00:00:58,319 --> 00:01:02,944
Metta is all the qualities you would expect of yourself as a good friend

12
00:01:03,682 --> 00:01:04,724
or of a good friend.

13
00:01:07,487 --> 00:01:13,254
And it's the basis of our relationship to each other, to all beings really, a sense of care.

14
00:01:15,819 --> 00:01:19,283
And when we've got that established, the other two illimitables, as they're called.

15
00:01:20,084 --> 00:01:24,269
Illimitable because they can be developed indefinitely, a bit like number.

16
00:01:25,331 --> 00:01:28,375
No matter how big your number you can conceive, you can always have one.

17
00:01:31,611 --> 00:01:42,167
So when we have that attitude of goodwill towards somebody, and if they fall into misfortune, compassion, a desire to help, rises naturally.

18
00:01:43,808 --> 00:01:49,176
And if they enjoy good fortune, we're happy for them.

19
00:01:52,019 --> 00:02:01,212
Equanimity, which is the other illimitable, of course, sits underneath these three, stops them corrupting into their, what's known as near enemy.

20
00:02:01,885 --> 00:02:09,812
Love corrupting into attachment, whereby we confuse liking somebody with love.

21
00:02:09,831 --> 00:02:11,013
Compassion into grief.

22
00:02:13,574 --> 00:02:14,776
And joy into excitement.

23
00:02:17,758 --> 00:02:19,099
This is self-indulgence, really.

24
00:02:22,521 --> 00:02:26,125
So metta in the Buddha's teaching is really part and parcel of the whole practice.

25
00:02:26,406 --> 00:02:31,469
And he asks us to maintain that goodwill throughout the day with awareness.

26
00:02:31,973 --> 00:02:39,080
So to live consciously with a good heart.

27
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:43,825
Now the one thing we mustn't do is to confuse goodwill, this metta, with an emotion.

28
00:02:47,209 --> 00:02:49,512
It's an attitude, it's a way of relating.

29
00:02:50,211 --> 00:02:56,878
So that you can have goodwill and act in a friendly way, even though you don't feel like it.

30
00:02:57,259 --> 00:02:58,420
You might not like the person.

31
00:03:00,182 --> 00:03:01,204
They might not like you.

32
00:03:03,175 --> 00:03:04,956
This is what's meant by loving your enemies.

33
00:03:06,899 --> 00:03:07,659
You don't have to like them.

34
00:03:11,223 --> 00:03:14,045
That's one of the gifts of a spiritual companion.

35
00:03:14,586 --> 00:03:15,448
You don't have to like them.

36
00:03:17,469 --> 00:03:18,631
But they're there as support.

37
00:03:24,296 --> 00:03:30,263
And as we practice that of course the heart does begin to respond and you can experience delightful feelings.

38
00:03:32,402 --> 00:03:35,606
Then the danger is that we begin to practice method just to feel good.

39
00:03:35,986 --> 00:03:37,449
So it becomes a selfish practice.

40
00:03:42,635 --> 00:03:46,159
The traditional blessings are may you be safe.

41
00:03:46,180 --> 00:03:50,925
So everybody wants to be safe from danger, danger outside, danger from within ourselves.

42
00:03:53,188 --> 00:03:54,751
From financial crises.

43
00:03:56,873 --> 00:03:57,955
Everybody wants to be well.

44
00:03:59,486 --> 00:04:01,628
Everybody wants to be free of mental distress.

45
00:04:01,649 --> 00:04:04,372
Everybody wants to be happy, fulfilled.

46
00:04:07,515 --> 00:04:12,842
And to have a certain ease with life.

47
00:04:14,383 --> 00:04:19,809
Not to be always in conflict with it.

48
00:04:19,829 --> 00:04:20,889
To live contented.

49
00:04:21,190 --> 00:04:24,434
Contentment is the mark of the fully liberated person.

50
00:04:25,475 --> 00:04:26,495
This is the way it is.

51
00:04:27,637 --> 00:04:28,819
It's not a resignation.

52
00:04:29,204 --> 00:04:30,706
This is the way it is, what can we do?

53
00:04:32,670 --> 00:04:33,872
Contentment.

54
00:04:33,891 --> 00:04:38,821
And that contentment leads to a certain harmony working with the situation.

55
00:04:40,624 --> 00:04:41,985
Even when it's not particularly pleasant.

56
00:04:42,826 --> 00:04:46,553
Contented and in harmony with the world.

57
00:04:47,675 --> 00:04:48,656
So those are our blessings.

58
00:04:49,499 --> 00:04:51,161
May you be safe, well and happy.

59
00:04:51,783 --> 00:04:54,266
Live contented, in harmony with the world.

60
00:04:56,591 --> 00:04:59,156
We begin with the particular, especially those who've helped us.

61
00:04:59,255 --> 00:05:02,360
So with gratitude, goodwill arises naturally.

62
00:05:04,002 --> 00:05:13,216
And then to near and dear, friends, neutral people, the people we see every day, maybe when we travel, our neighbours, but we don't know them.

63
00:05:17,221 --> 00:05:21,187
Even people we're familiar with on television, radio, but we don't actually know them.

64
00:05:24,012 --> 00:05:26,295
We can even offer goodwill to a politician.

65
00:05:26,949 --> 00:05:32,516
Then there's ourselves, of course.

66
00:05:32,536 --> 00:05:33,677
We mustn't forget ourselves.

67
00:05:34,577 --> 00:05:36,759
So we offer those same blessings to ourselves.

68
00:05:37,259 --> 00:05:41,004
And then when the heart is softened, we can bring in somebody we find difficult.

69
00:05:41,024 --> 00:05:46,649
Not that they are difficult, we just find them difficult.

70
00:05:46,670 --> 00:05:49,853
Then we begin to spread it outwards, first of all, to each other, here, now.

71
00:05:50,874 --> 00:05:53,937
And to our neighbours, so you can relocate to where you live.

72
00:05:55,569 --> 00:06:01,817
all the people in our country, all the peoples of Europe, and finally all people on earth.

73
00:06:03,338 --> 00:06:07,884
Sorry, then after all people on earth, sorry, to all beings, all beings in all directions.

74
00:06:07,903 --> 00:06:11,908
And we'll do the six directions, before, behind, left, right, below and above.

75
00:06:15,110 --> 00:06:20,177
And we end with a chant, which means may all beings be happy.

76
00:06:29,523 --> 00:06:32,115
So if you wish to continue standing, you can do this standing.

77
00:06:32,697 --> 00:06:35,752
But if you'd like to sit, then we can take a posture.

78
00:07:06,225 --> 00:07:08,689
So remember that you're not trying to feel good.

79
00:07:08,910 --> 00:07:11,593
That makes the practice very nice.

80
00:07:13,396 --> 00:07:17,944
You're just trying to develop an attitude and you do that by little internal acts of will.

81
00:07:19,024 --> 00:07:23,692
That's why at the end of a sitting we can make these little resolutions and eventually they'll sort of make their way through.

82
00:07:32,384 --> 00:07:35,490
So let's bring to mind somebody who has helped us in our lives.

83
00:07:39,266 --> 00:07:41,209
As we pictured them before us there.

84
00:07:44,031 --> 00:07:47,033
May you be safe, well and happy.

85
00:07:47,855 --> 00:07:50,918
May you live contented in harmony with the world.

86
00:07:54,081 --> 00:07:55,562
Just gently repeat that towards.

87
00:07:57,324 --> 00:07:59,665
Now some people feel a warmth in their heart.

88
00:07:59,685 --> 00:08:00,086
Why not?

89
00:08:00,786 --> 00:08:01,927
Some people have a colour.

90
00:08:03,329 --> 00:08:03,910
Doesn't matter.

91
00:08:04,009 --> 00:08:08,733
Whatever helps to develop that attitude is fine.

92
00:08:27,276 --> 00:08:34,716
bringing to mind those who are near and dear to us.

93
00:08:34,735 --> 00:08:37,582
May you be safe, well and happy.

94
00:08:38,365 --> 00:08:41,572
May you live contented, in harmony with the world.

95
00:09:03,759 --> 00:09:07,086
We can bring to mind friends, people at work, whomever we wish.

96
00:09:14,860 --> 00:09:17,485
May you be safe, well and happy.

97
00:09:19,168 --> 00:09:22,596
May you live contented, in harmony with the world.

98
00:09:43,956 --> 00:09:56,176
And to my neutral people, people we see but don't know, offering them the same quality of goodwill.

99
00:09:56,196 --> 00:09:58,659
May you be safe, well and happy.

100
00:10:00,221 --> 00:10:03,466
May you live contented, in harmony with the world.

101
00:10:28,860 --> 00:10:31,663
Turning now that stream of goodwill towards ourselves.

102
00:10:33,485 --> 00:10:36,469
May I be safe, well and happy.

103
00:10:37,610 --> 00:10:40,293
May I live contentedly in harmony with the world.

104
00:10:46,539 --> 00:10:51,686
When we do this practice, especially towards ourselves, it can feel inauthentic because we don't feel it.

105
00:10:53,607 --> 00:10:55,289
But that's the confusion.

106
00:10:57,532 --> 00:11:02,599
Whether we feel it or not, we make these intentions.

107
00:11:02,619 --> 00:11:04,562
And it's the intentions which are authentic.

108
00:11:04,721 --> 00:11:06,884
Put your identity into the intentions.

109
00:11:12,873 --> 00:11:16,518
May I be safe, well and happy.

110
00:11:17,519 --> 00:11:21,345
May I live contented, in harmony with the world.

111
00:11:38,470 --> 00:11:41,557
And into the heart of goodwill someone we find difficult.

112
00:11:46,707 --> 00:11:48,932
May you be safe, well and happy.

113
00:11:49,533 --> 00:11:53,442
May you live contented, in harmony with the world.

114
00:12:25,585 --> 00:12:29,236
And we can begin now to radiate it outwards to each other.

115
00:12:31,043 --> 00:12:33,793
May we be safe, well and happy.

116
00:12:34,534 --> 00:12:37,806
May we live contented, in harmony with the world.

117
00:13:21,205 --> 00:13:26,119
And we can begin to radiate it outward to our neighbours, so here we can relocate to where we live.

118
00:13:29,769 --> 00:13:32,255
May you be safe, well and happy.

119
00:13:33,399 --> 00:13:36,327
May you live contented, in harmony with the world.

120
00:14:10,143 --> 00:14:18,229
Radiating outward to all the people in our country.

121
00:14:45,495 --> 00:14:54,797
And you'll notice here that unlike in vipassana where we want to shut down the imagining thinking mind, now we're using it skillfully to develop attitude.

122
00:15:13,001 --> 00:15:16,126
Radiating outward to all the peoples of Europe.

123
00:16:04,758 --> 00:16:06,902
And from there to all people on earth.

124
00:16:06,922 --> 00:16:30,360
And as you hover over places where there's war, destitution caused by natural disasters, poverty, all sorts of suffering, just hover above those places and offer your goodwill.

125
00:17:26,467 --> 00:17:29,852
Now we can begin to radiate it outwards in the six directions.

126
00:17:30,413 --> 00:17:32,615
First of all, to all beings before us.

127
00:17:34,940 --> 00:17:37,403
May you be safe, well and happy.

128
00:17:37,423 --> 00:17:40,287
May you live contented in harmony with the world.

129
00:17:51,723 --> 00:17:53,487
All beings behind us.

130
00:18:16,196 --> 00:18:17,519
All beings to our left.

131
00:18:37,207 --> 00:18:38,509
All beings to our right.

132
00:18:54,587 --> 00:19:21,375
All beings below us.

133
00:19:21,395 --> 00:19:22,856
All beings above us.

134
00:19:38,682 --> 00:19:45,586
and to all beings in all directions.

135
00:20:07,690 --> 00:20:10,874
And I'd like to offer you another format which you may find useful.

136
00:20:12,915 --> 00:20:15,679
Turning that stream of goodwill towards ourselves.

137
00:20:18,321 --> 00:20:25,210
May I be free of greed and selfishness.

138
00:20:25,230 --> 00:20:28,173
May I be free of hatred and ill will.

139
00:20:33,818 --> 00:20:37,123
May I be free of fear and anxiety.

140
00:20:43,414 --> 00:20:52,963
May I be free of ignorance and delusion.

141
00:20:52,983 --> 00:21:06,497
May I be kind and gentle sympathetic and benevolent.

142
00:21:06,517 --> 00:21:09,759
May I be forgiving and compassionate.

143
00:21:15,832 --> 00:21:20,299
May I be joyful and rejoice in the success of others.

144
00:21:28,575 --> 00:21:31,259
May I be peace loving and calm.

145
00:21:37,691 --> 00:21:40,236
May I be liberated of all my suffering.

146
00:21:47,101 --> 00:21:51,126
May I experience the peace and bliss of Nibbana.

147
00:22:00,220 --> 00:22:03,945
And radiating that out to all beings in all directions.

148
00:22:05,989 --> 00:22:10,154
May all beings be free of greed and selfishness.

149
00:22:15,636 --> 00:22:40,834
May all beings be free of hatred and ill will May all beings be free of fear and anxiety May all beings be free of ignorance and delusion

150
00:22:47,227 --> 00:23:02,186
May all beings be kind and gentle sympathetic and benevolent.

151
00:23:02,207 --> 00:23:05,791
May all beings be forgiving and compassionate.

152
00:23:12,521 --> 00:23:26,976
May all beings be joyful and rejoice in the success of others.

153
00:23:26,996 --> 00:23:37,967
May all beings be peace loving and kind.

154
00:23:37,987 --> 00:23:41,230
May all beings be liberated of all their sufferings.

155
00:23:47,115 --> 00:23:56,612
May all beings experience the peace and bliss of your God.

156
00:23:56,632 --> 00:24:01,721
Sabae sata sukita hantu.

157
00:24:01,740 --> 00:24:08,752
Sabae sata sukita hantu.

158
00:24:09,104 --> 00:24:33,913
Sāve Sāca Sūdhita Aum Tu Sāve Sāca Sūdhita Aum Tu Sāve Sadhu Sadhu

